<p>The alert dialog created in the onclick reappears every single time I dismiss it in an infinite loop. This occurs in both Chrome and Firefox. This is my first day learning Javascript so please be gentle.</p>  <p>Is there a way to make the alert dialog appear only once?</p>  <p>This might be a problem with my computer. If so, what do I do to fix that?</p>  <pre><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; &lt;html&gt; &lt;body&gt;  &lt;h1&gt;What Can JavaScript Do?&lt;/h1&gt;  &lt;p id="demo"&gt;JavaScript can change the style of an HTML element.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;"The text should turn red and one alert dialog should appear on click."&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;script&gt; function changeFontRed() {     var x = document.getElementById("demo");     x.style.color = "red";     console.log("Hello World!");     window.alert("Hello World!");     x.removeEventListener("onclick", changeFontRed(), false);     x.addEventListener("onclick", changeFontBlue()); }  function changeFontBlue() {     var x = document.getElementById("demo");                x.style.color = "blue";     x.removeEventListener("onclick", changeFontBlue(), false);     x.addEventListener("onclick", changeFontRed()); } &lt;/script&gt;  &lt;button type="button" onclick="changeFontRed()"&gt;Click Me!&lt;/button&gt;  &lt;/body&gt; &lt;/html&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Thanks guys.</p>